ing ellipticals (E-SRs) than to S0s, suggesting that E-FRs are not\nsimply S0s viewed face-on. 3) At fixed $\\sigma_0$, more luminous S0s and E-FRs\nare younger, more metal rich and less $\\alpha$-enhanced. Evidently for these\ngalaxies, the usual statement that 'massive galaxies are older' is not true if\n$\\sigma_0$ is held fixed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 May 2020 17:59:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-27"}
